body:
Hello,
when design has modules with nonsense default parameters Yosys will give Warnings  like:
"Range select out of bounds on signal `\s_in' at test.v:6: Setting 3 MSB bits to undef."
In cases where codebase has many hundred of instantiated modules this will be issue.
If some of instantiated modules will get poor parameters it's hard to find "real" warnings because of many default parameter Warnings. 
I suggest improvement where Default parameter Warnings will be different compared to parameter check made for instantiated modules.

Here is simple code as an example.

```
module sub_module (s_in, s_out);
parameter NUM = 10; //default
input [7:0] s_in;
output [3:0] s_out;

assign s_out = s_in[NUM:0];

endmodule


module top ( m_out, m_in);
parameter NUM = 3;
input [7:0] m_in;
output [3:0] m_out;

sub_module #(NUM)
    sub_1 (.s_in (m_in), .s_out(m_out));
endmodule
```

Cheers

